Alfred Mann April 1917 September 2006 was writer musical theory and Professor Musicology the Eastman School Music University Rochester Alfred Mann left Germany before World War and moved Italy where only could stay shortly 1938 Mann had leave Italy because Mussolini mandate and Mann moved the USA After long career Mann became Professor Musicology the Eastman School 1980 retiring and becoming Professor Emeritus 1987 1943 Mann made the first translation Johann Joseph Fuxs Gradus Parnassum into English The translation contained the preface pages 139 and page 279 the original work 1958 Mann translated into English the part Gradus Parnassum that concerned the composition fugue pages 140 217 the original work 